      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the logic used by those proponents often leads to the implication of a hierarchy, suggesting that certain groups possess a biological predisposition for higher cognitive functions than others. They interpret heritability estimates to mean that the observed differences in average scores reflect underlying, fixed genetic differences between racial groups. This perspective directly translates statistical variance into a ranking of inherent intellectual capacity across different populations. It is this direct leap from genetic correlation to biological ranking that is the most heavily criticized aspect of their arguments.",
